  "prompt": "If I delete my Tinder account and uninstall the app, does my profile still show to those I've matched with?",
  "response": "No, deleting your Tinder account means your profile will no longer be visible to anyone, including those you've matched with.\n\nHere's a breakdown of what happens:\n\n*   **Disappearance from the app:** Once deleted, your profile is removed from Tinder's system and is no longer searchable or visible to other users.\n\n*   **Matches can't see you:** Your matches will see that the conversation is gone or that the profile is no longer available. They won't be able to message you or view your profile.\n\n*   **Irreversible:** Deletion is permanent. If you decide to use Tinder again, you'll need to create a new account.\n\nUninstalling the app alone is not enough to remove your profile. You must delete the account within the app settings.\n",
